  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">REACH ACT Alliance IRQ151 Support to Displaced People and hosts in Iraq</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall goal is to meet the life-saving needs of the most vulnerable Iraqi IDPs (and host community) Iraqi Kurdistan, through provision of food, NFIs, health and hygiene kits and cash assistance, and increased livelihoods opportunities.  This project will provide food security for 8,400 families (KRG region of northern Iraq); WASH (health and hygiene kits and women&apos;s dignity items) to 960 families, NFI&apos;s (kitchen sets, stoves, mattresses, blankets, pillows) to 540 families, summarization NFIs (air cooler, plastic sheeting, water cooler, jerry cans) to 480 families, Protection (cash assistance) of $400 to 120 families, Livelihoods (cash for work) providing for 1080 families, Livelihoods (cash grants) providing for 20 families.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will bring about significant change to the lives of those in Iraq affected by the most recent humanitarian crisis.Those who have fled their homes leaving behind their livelihoods, their education, and most of their worldly goods. The immediate relief provided by REACH in this programme provides them with sufficient basic food and non-food items to ensure that their basic living and nutritonal needs are met. For the most vulnerable cash assistance is key to ensure that they are not forced into negative coping strategies (including prostitution, crime, and excessive borrowing), the same can be said of the other forms of distribution in terms of avoiding these issues and affording some level of dignity to families in desperate need of food and basic hygeine supplies. 
The livelihoods element of this project is key to re-building lives and building resilience .</narrative>
  </description>
